title: Filth Everywhere Music Video
description: Teri's playful J-pop song.

title: The Bus
description: When Rocky suggests the Elmore Junior High kids skip school, the bus is boarded by criminals, who seem to want to teach them the importance of school attendance. The masked culprits are clearly the children's parents faking a heist to teach them a lesson. But when the police get involved for real, it becomes clear the parents aren't the ones pulling the strings.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Telly
description: Grady thinks the TV show they are watching is awful and decides to get the gang together to make their own show.

title: The Puppets
description: While searching the attic for items to put in their yard sale, Gumball and Darwin stumble upon a load of their old toys. Darwin is especially pleased when he finds his old puppets, Frank and Howdy. However, as Darwin starts playing with them again, Gumball gradually realizes that Frank and Howdy are actually playing with Darwin...

title: The Future
description: Gumball, Darwin and Banana Joe investigate Banana Barbara's mysterious disappearance and uncover an old rival's shadowy scheme in the process.

title: Gumball: Elmore News 3
description: From a high-speed police chase to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top hard-hitting local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger is the man to bring you the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Weird Food
description: Puppet Gumball imagines some weird food then tries it.

title: Banana Song Music Video
description: Banana fails dramatically.

title: The Heart
description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

title: The Decisions
description: When everything goes wrong in Darwin's life, he begins to suspect that Gumball's bad influence might be to blame. Darwin decides to go elsewhere for guidance and finds a new mentor in Alan. But maybe it's time Darwin started making his own decisions.

title: The Cycle
description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Mr Wilson has been picking on their Dad for most of his life; ever since he humiliated Richard with a high school prank. The kids try to work Dad through it but when their efforts fail, they realize that getting back at Mr Wilson is the only way to break the cycle.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Spoons
description: Frank has taken Grady's beloved house Spoon. Grady is forced into a dance off to win it back.

title: Singing Music Video
description: Join the citizens of Elmore for a song and dance spectacular.

title: Hairy Lady Music Video

title: Waiting for Gumball: BirdPlaneBird
description: Darwin and BirdPlaneBird try to share a refreshing drink, it turns out to be hard as a puppet.

title: The Misunderstandings
description: Gumball has misunderstood about his date with Penny. He thought they were meeting for dinner but they were actually meeting for lunch at a Diner called Dinner. He runs to the mall but everyone he meets on the way seems to misunderstand him in a different way. Once he finally does get to the mall, it seems all his misunderstandings have caught up with him.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Insulting Voices
description: Gumball and Darwin play with smaller hand puppets of themselves who mimic their voices very badly.

title: The Factory
description: Gumball and Darwin follow Nicole to the Rainbow Factory for Bring your Kids to Work Day. They are expecting a magical place full of dreams and wonder but it turns out to be a little less magical than they'd hoped. Despite the fact nobody wants them there, they end up saving the factory from being closed down.

title: The Stink
description: Gumball decides to put Mr. Small's eco-friendly principles to the test but it doesn't quite go as planned. Mr. Small disappears after deciding to leave the modern world behind. But on the plus side they discover that the Great Stink-Ape of Elmore Woods is definitely not extinct.

title: How I Like My Food Music Video
description: Richard's food ballad.

title: The List
description: When the kids find out that Mom's life hasn't panned out exactly as she'd hoped, they try to make her day a bit easier by taking on her chores. However, they accidentally grab her bucket list instead of her to-do list and end up attempting to tick off all of Nicole's life goals.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Infinite Loop
description: Gumball and Darwin discover smaller hand puppet  versions of themselves and get caught in an infinite loop of puppets.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Clean
description: Grady is determined to tidy up the house and persuades Howdy and Frank to help. While cleaning Frank unexpectedly discovers the love of his life under a bin bag.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Cool to Be Felt
description: Gumball and Darwin realize they are puppets and it's seriously cool.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Bored
description: Frank is bored and pesters the others to entertain him for the afternoon.

title: The Ollie
description: When Darwin asks Gumball to teach him how to skate, Gumball makes sure he covers every aspect of the skating lifestyle from wearing the right gear, using the right terms and choosing the right board. But when Darwin finally gets his wheels rolling, he realizes there might be one important aspect of skating Gumball hasn't taught him.

title: The Web
description: Gumball and Darwin realize that the adult residents of Elmore are dangerously naive when it comes to being safe online. In fact they are in serious need of the boys help with even the simplest of tasks. And no more so than their mom, Nicole.

title: The Deal
description: When Mom wins Employee of the Month at the Rainbow factory, Richard feels like he is never celebrated for all the work he does at home. Nicole is suspicious of how much he actually does, but when Richard goes on strike, his important role in keeping things under control becomes painfully clear...

title: The Best
description: No matter what Gumball does, Carmen thinks she knows better. Gumball attempts to gain the moral high ground but fails spectacularly.  He decides that self-improvement isn't his style. The only option he has left is to bring Carmen down to his level.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Gnomes
description: Gumball and Darwin realize that anything they imagine will become real in Puppet World, but all they can think of are Garden Gnomes.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Beards
description: Puppet Gumball and Darwin discover they can grow very weird beards.

title: Waiting for Gumball: Grump
description: Frank is getting grumpy waiting for Gumball and Darwin to return so Grady and Howdy throw a party to cheer him up.

title: Pluto's Lament Music Video
description: Pluto feels left out.

title: The Master
description: Dad decides to resolve the Watterson family's differences through the power and magic of his favorite roleplaying game. As they embark on the adventure of a lifetime and battle mythical creatures, will they finally manage to put their differences aside and work together?
